Aemilius Paulus, L. (29, 61, 75, 82), cos. 13.c. 219 and 216, killed in his second consulship in the battle of Cannae. He was father of the victor of Pydna (see below), and grandfather of the younger AfricanuS. His daughter married the elder Africanus·

Aemilius Paulus Macedonicus, L. (15, 82), cos, 13.C. 182 and 168, son of the foregoing. In his second consulship Macedonia and the war against Perseus (Third Macedonian War) fell to his lot. He ended the war by his victory at Pydna, B.C. 168.
